From: chat-template-patches
Subject: [Q3.6-5] <|think_off|> / <|think_on|> system-message sentinels (R3 port + extension)

Targets: templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja (state after Q3.6-1 + Q3.6-2 + Q3.6-3 + Q3.6-4 applied)

Two new system-message sentinels for per-request thinking control on
runtimes that don't reliably pass `chat_template_kwargs={"enable_thinking": ...}`:

- `<|think_off|>` (R3 port from Qwen3.5): when present in the merged
  system message, force `enable_thinking=False`. The sentinel is
  stripped from the rendered system block.
- `<|think_on|>` (NEW for this catalog, sourced from froggeric's
  Qwen-Fixed-Chat-Templates): when present, force `enable_thinking=True`.
  Useful when the runtime defaults thinking off and the user wants to
  override per-request.

Sentinel detection wins over the raw `enable_thinking` kwarg (sentinels
take precedence). Implementation uses a namespace `ns_flags` so the
generation-prompt block can read the post-sentinel state regardless of
whether a kwarg was passed.

Conflict policy: when BOTH sentinels appear in the merged system text,
the **rightmost-in-text** one wins (deterministic; matches "last write
wins" intuition for an explicit per-request override appended to an
inherited default). Codex adversarial review (2026-05-06) caught that
the original code-order processing always let `<|think_on|>` win
regardless of textual order; rfind-based comparison fixes that.

This is the delimited-tag form of the sentinel, matching Qwen's own
control-token convention. The hardened form prevents collisions with
documentation excerpts or file paths that might mention the literal
string `/no_thinking` (the original P5 sentinel suffered this issue).

minja-safety (2026-06): the sentinel strip uses `split|join`, NOT the
`.replace()` method. llama.cpp's minja silently drops the ENTIRE string
when the replaced target is at index 0 (a system prompt that starts with
`<|think_off|>`), which would erase the whole system block on C++ engines.
`split|join` is byte-identical under jinja2 and safe on minja. Independently
surfaced by froggeric (Qwen-Fixed-Chat-Templates v20).

Stacks on Q3.6-1 + Q3.6-2 + Q3.6-3 + Q3.6-4. Diff is against the
Q3.6-4-applied state.

--- a/templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja
+++ b/templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja
@@ -42,6 +42,11 @@
 {%- if not messages %}
     {{- raise_exception('No messages provided.') }}
 {%- endif %}
+{#- Q3.6-5: thinking-toggle sentinel state. Initialized from the kwarg (if set), then overridden by `<|think_off|>` / `<|think_on|>` sentinels detected in the merged system message below. The generation-prompt block at the bottom of the template reads ns_flags.enable_thinking instead of the raw kwarg. -#}
+{%- set ns_flags = namespace(enable_thinking=none) %}
+{%- if enable_thinking is defined %}
+    {%- set ns_flags.enable_thinking = enable_thinking %}
+{%- endif %}
 {%- set num_sys = 0 %}
 {%- set merged_system = '' %}
 {%- if messages[0].role == 'system' or messages[0].role == 'developer' %}
@@ -56,6 +61,18 @@
         {%- set num_sys = 1 %}
     {%- endif %}
 {%- endif %}
+{#- Q3.6-5: detect and strip thinking-toggle sentinels in the merged system message. When BOTH appear, the rightmost-in-text sentinel wins (deterministic; matches "last write wins" intuition for an explicit per-request override appended to an inherited default). -#}
+{%- set _think_off_pos = merged_system.rfind('<|think_off|>') %}
+{%- set _think_on_pos = merged_system.rfind('<|think_on|>') %}
+{%- if _think_off_pos >= 0 or _think_on_pos >= 0 %}
+    {%- if _think_off_pos > _think_on_pos %}
+        {%- set ns_flags.enable_thinking = false %}
+    {%- else %}
+        {%- set ns_flags.enable_thinking = true %}
+    {%- endif %}
+    {#- Q3.6-5: strip both sentinels with split|join, NOT `.replace()` — llama.cpp's minja silently drops the whole string when the replaced target sits at index 0 (e.g. a system prompt that STARTS with `<|think_off|>`). split|join is byte-identical under jinja2 and safe on C++ engines. (froggeric Qwen-Fixed-Chat-Templates v20.) -#}
+    {%- set merged_system = (merged_system.split('<|think_off|>')|join('')).split('<|think_on|>')|join('')|trim %}
+{%- endif %}
 {%- if tools and tools is iterable and tools is not mapping %}
     {{- '<|im_start|>system\n' }}
     {{- "# Tools\n\nYou have access to the following functions:\n\n<tools>" }}
@@ -163,7 +180,8 @@
 {%- endfor %}
 {%- if add_generation_prompt %}
     {{- '<|im_start|>assistant\n' }}
-    {%- if enable_thinking is defined and enable_thinking is false %}
+    {#- Q3.6-5: read ns_flags.enable_thinking (sentinel-aware) instead of raw kwarg -#}
+    {%- if ns_flags.enable_thinking is false %}
         {{- '<think>\n\n</think>\n\n' }}
     {%- else %}
         {{- '<think>\n' }}
